00:02:50,804 --> 00:02:53,296
What have you got
against chickens?

3
00:02:53,407 --> 00:02:55,399
One got choked last
night, thanks to you.

4
00:02:55,475 --> 00:02:58,570
33-year-old male with
haemoptysis, fever.

5
00:02:58,645 --> 00:02:59,908
We can't even talk about it?

6
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:03,144
If you can't apologize, we
can't talk. And puncture wounds.

7
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:05,845
I'm not apologizing
for doing the right thing.

8
00:03:05,952 --> 00:03:08,114
Lying to me was
not the right thing.

9
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:10,987
Puncture wounds
are from a crucifixion.

10
00:03:14,961 --> 00:03:17,362
I lied to save
my patient's life.

11
00:03:17,431 --> 00:03:19,764
I didn't lie to you,
I lied to my boss.

12
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,299
Either of those
arguments working yet?

13
00:03:25,839 --> 00:03:29,276
Guess that means I don't have
to go to the wedding on Saturday.

14
00:03:29,342 --> 00:03:31,641
The hospital's
chairman of the board?

15
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:34,511
I'm not gonna stand him
up and neither are you.

16
00:03:34,614 --> 00:03:37,482
I loathe weddings and their
seven levels of hypocrisy.

17
00:03:37,584 --> 00:03:39,519
But you do seem awfully hissy,

18
00:03:39,619 --> 00:03:42,919
and there's an outside chance
I can get you drunk and score.

19
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:45,229
So as long as you don't
take it as an admission of guilt,

20
00:03:45,292 --> 00:03:47,454
sure, count me in.

21
00:03:47,761 --> 00:03:49,195
Bit too much honesty?

22
00:03:49,830 --> 00:03:51,992
You're also going to the
rehearsal dinner Friday night.

23
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:54,592
Dressy casual.

24
00:04:02,109 --> 00:04:03,600
House-keeping.

25
00:04:04,111 --> 00:04:07,843
Either you're crazy or you're
atoning for something naughty.

26
00:04:08,348 --> 00:04:09,646
And you're crazy.

27
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:11,614
He's a doctor.

28
00:04:11,685 --> 00:04:13,313
I'm not atoning for anything.

29
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:15,315
That answers that, thanks.

30
00:04:15,388 --> 00:04:19,849
My Marisa was diagnosed with terminal
brain cancer, stage IV glioblastoma.

31
00:04:20,227 --> 00:04:22,628
When the doctors said
she had two months to live,

32
00:04:24,231 --> 00:04:25,859
that's when I made my bargain.

33
00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:28,464
With your health
insurance carrier?

34
00:04:29,202 --> 00:04:30,397
With God.

35
00:04:30,537 --> 00:04:31,537
Oh!

36
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:35,372
I told him I would nail myself to a
cross every year he kept her alive.

37
00:04:35,809 --> 00:04:37,289
So how did that negotiation go?

38
00:04:37,377 --> 00:04:39,972
You lowballed with ear
piercing and God countered?

39
00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:44,307
Three weeks later, she was
cancer-free. That was four years ago.

40
00:04:44,384 --> 00:04:46,819
Pontius Pilate,
misunderstood oncologist.

41
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:49,186
Yeah. My ex-wife
thinks I'm crazy, too.

42
00:04:50,323 --> 00:04:51,985
She moved out the
first time I did this.

43
00:04:52,826 --> 00:04:55,318
At least your daughter
has one viable role model.

44
00:04:55,662 --> 00:04:57,392
You don't believe in God?
- I did.

45
00:04:57,497 --> 00:04:59,090
Then I grew my curly hairs.

46
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,744
So how do you think I was cured?

47
00:05:01,768 --> 00:05:03,862
Maybe you were
misdiagnosed in the first place.

48
00:05:03,937 --> 00:05:07,271
You have your answer,
Doctors. We have ours.

49
00:05:07,374 --> 00:05:10,902
Causal determinism, we are
hardwired to need answers.

50
00:05:11,611 --> 00:05:14,080
The caveman who heard
a rustle in the bushes

51
00:05:14,181 --> 00:05:15,258
and checked out
to see what it was

52
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,683
lived longer than the guy who
assumed it was just a breeze.

53
00:05:17,751 --> 00:05:19,219
The problem is,

54
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:22,051
when we don't find a logical
answer, we settle for a stupid one.

55
00:05:23,223 --> 00:05:25,783
Ritual is what happens
when we run out of rational.

56
00:05:25,892 --> 00:05:28,088
If you're done mocking him,
we need to prep for an LP.

57
00:05:28,195 --> 00:05:31,927
Good. Another hole in him
should really make God's day.

58
00:05:38,872 --> 00:05:40,067
Why are you late?

59
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:42,109
Your next dental
appointment isn't until January

60
00:05:42,209 --> 00:05:44,542
and you just saw your
GP eight days ago.

61
00:05:44,611 --> 00:05:47,479
Think stage IV glioblastoma
in an eight-year-old

62
00:05:47,581 --> 00:05:48,913
can disappear in three weeks?

63
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:51,051
Had a flat tire. Your
patient has cancer?

64
00:05:51,117 --> 00:05:53,279
Your tires have got less
than 5,000 miles on them.

65
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,889
No, and neither does
my patient's daughter.

66
00:05:55,956 --> 00:05:58,619
I hit a piece of rebar
near a construction site.

67
00:05:59,292 --> 00:06:02,262
In three weeks?
It's highly unlikely.

68
00:06:02,329 --> 00:06:04,560
There's no construction site
between here and your home.

69
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:07,097
I agree, I think it was
a misdiagnosed cyst.

70
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,795
But there is one between
here and my dry cleaner.

71
00:06:09,903 --> 00:06:14,034
It could be a misdiagnosis or it
could be spontaneous remission, but...

72
00:06:14,774 --> 00:06:16,766
Why would I lie about
this? I don't know yet.

73
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:19,397
But you would've dropped off
your tie, it's got a mustard stain.

74
00:06:25,952 --> 00:06:27,750
I was buying an engagement ring.

75
00:06:28,555 --> 00:06:30,421
I'm gonna propose
to Sam at the wedding.

76
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:33,085
That is the second stupidest
thing I've heard today.

77
00:06:33,793 --> 00:06:35,261
And I'm surprised
how close you came.

78
00:06:36,296 --> 00:06:37,740
You didn't need to
buy her a new ring.

79
00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:39,733
Isn't the first one good
for all-you-can-marry?

80
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:42,997
I assume you haven't
apologized to Cuddy yet.

81
00:06:43,103 --> 00:06:44,503
Your stupidity
demands equal time.

82
00:06:44,604 --> 00:06:46,232
Nothing to apologize for.

83
00:06:48,275 --> 00:06:49,470
Pretend to apologize.

84
00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:50,542
You want me to lie?

85
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:51,890
There's a lovely symmetry to it.

86
00:06:51,945 --> 00:06:53,825
A lie got you into it,
a lie gets you out of it.

87
00:06:53,914 --> 00:06:56,611
Everybody lies.
I'm sure Cuddy...

88
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,579
Just need to give her a chance.

89
00:07:04,124 --> 00:07:06,491
Yeah, that must've
been what I meant.

90
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,856
Have you seen the bride-to-be?

91
00:07:08,962 --> 00:07:11,727
Gorgeous woman half
his age. He's a lucky guy.

92
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:13,357
Yeah. For a while.

93
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,626
My father's 19 years
older than my mother

94
00:07:15,702 --> 00:07:17,502
and they've been happily
married for 32 years.

95
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:20,439
I'm guessing your dad
wasn't on the Forbes 400

96
00:07:20,507 --> 00:07:22,499
and your mom didn't
look like a swimsuit model.

97
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,601
Sorry, that didn't
come out right.

98
00:07:25,679 --> 00:07:30,549
My father was the classics chair at
Columbia and my mother was his student.

99
00:07:30,717 --> 00:07:34,051
His gorgeous student.

100
00:07:34,154 --> 00:07:37,181
What's it mean when somebody
takes their cell phone into the bathroom

101
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,450
when they're taking a shower?

102
00:07:39,726 --> 00:07:42,821
Means they don't want you to
check their calls, e-mails or texts.

103
00:07:42,896 --> 00:07:44,489
If we're talking
about your wife,

104
00:07:44,698 --> 00:07:47,725
it means the chickens
are coming home to roost.

105
00:07:48,868 --> 00:07:51,133
Taub has been known to dabble.

106
00:07:51,204 --> 00:07:52,297
Used to be.

107
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:56,476
Maybe it's just a habit. I do that
with my cell phone and I live alone.

108
00:07:56,543 --> 00:08:00,241
She has a meeting
today at 1:30, at a hotel.

109
00:08:00,347 --> 00:08:02,680
I'm gonna go with
the chicken thing.

110
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:07,580
Negative for toxocara,
bacteroides, ascaris, everything.

111
00:08:07,687 --> 00:08:10,555
So what looks like an infection
but doesn't test like one?

112
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:13,651
Animals.

113
00:08:13,727 --> 00:08:15,287
I'm sure your wife's
just seeing a dude.

114
00:08:16,730 --> 00:08:19,723
Patient works for Morgan
Timber Works, card's in the file.

115
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,393
"Specializing in
stables, barns and stalls."

116
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,494
He works around
animals. Rhodococcus equi.

117
00:08:24,571 --> 00:08:26,437
Unless this guy's
sleeping in the manger.

118
00:08:26,539 --> 00:08:28,940
Or has a history of open wounds.

119
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:39,743
We think you have rhodococcus
equi, a horse infection.

120
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:42,789
It's pretty rare in humans but
easily treatable with antibiotics.

121
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:44,482
Does it make
your teeth fall out?

122
00:08:44,557 --> 00:08:45,557
No.

123
00:08:52,766 --> 00:08:56,430
Then again, maybe we were wrong.

124
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:05,342
Fever, coughing up
blood, coughing up teeth.

125
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:10,984
Either God sweetened the deal
with a no-flossing clause, or...

126
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:12,417
Radiation sickness.

127
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:15,045
Yeah, maybe the carpenter
builds microwave ovens.

128
00:09:15,155 --> 00:09:16,179
Kaposi sarcoma?

129
00:09:16,256 --> 00:09:17,690
No skin lesions.

130
00:09:17,757 --> 00:09:21,387
Heavy metal poisoning fits,
canned tuna, sushi, lead paint.

131
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:24,521
Heavy metal it is. Do a home
search and a peripheral smear.

132
00:09:24,597 --> 00:09:27,226
I can't. I have a
personal errand to run.

133
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,893
Trying to catch
your wife cheating?

134
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,337
Why would you say that?

135
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:37,536
Missing mojo, posture
slumped, expression defeated,

136
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:40,603
you didn't try to back up your
theory. And Chase told me.

137
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:43,846
Go, find your mojo.

138
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:54,284
Shopkeeper, I
need a patient file.

139
00:09:54,761 --> 00:09:55,761
Ask records.

140
00:09:55,829 --> 00:09:56,956
Not one of our patients',

141
00:09:57,063 --> 00:09:59,055
my patient's daughter.
Ask your patient.

142
00:09:59,132 --> 00:10:01,192
He thinks I only want
it to debunk his faith.

143
00:10:01,534 --> 00:10:02,934
And why would he think that?

144
00:10:03,036 --> 00:10:06,029
Because he's strangely
perceptive for an idiot.

145
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:10,870
And I'm going to violate patient
privacy laws just to keep you happy?

146
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:15,040
You keep me happy, I return
the favor. Think of it as tat for tit.

147
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:18,950
When we're at work, we need
to focus on our work thoughts.

148
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:22,455
Why are you wearing that?

149
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:24,456
It's my dressy casual.
What do you think?

150
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:26,389
You look like Wilson.

151
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:28,254
It looks weird.

152
00:10:28,728 --> 00:10:30,424
But you knew I'd think that,

153
00:10:30,563 --> 00:10:32,464
which makes me wonder
why you look disappointed.

154
00:10:32,565 --> 00:10:34,625
If you prick me, do I not bleed?

155
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:40,966
You knew I wouldn't like it but
you thought I would say I did.

156
00:10:41,074 --> 00:10:44,306
That's what this is about. You're
trying to trap me into lying to you.

157
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:46,743
You sure? That
sounds so juvenile.

158
00:10:53,119 --> 00:10:55,679
You're okay with burglary now?

159
00:10:55,755 --> 00:10:56,984
I asked his permission.

160
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,518
The reason we
don't ask permission

161
00:11:00,627 --> 00:11:03,028
is we're afraid the patient
is going to hide something.

162
00:11:03,129 --> 00:11:04,893
But our patient
hasn't been home,

163
00:11:04,964 --> 00:11:06,660
lives alone, doesn't
have any help,

164
00:11:06,766 --> 00:11:08,667
and has no motive
to hide anything.

165
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:10,993
You ask for his key, too?

166
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:12,595
Oh! Doesn't have one.

167
00:11:19,712 --> 00:11:21,544
And now we know why.

168
00:11:22,782 --> 00:11:24,546
You think he's crazy?

169
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:27,979
Crucifixion's pretty convincing
evidence. Lead paint?

170
00:11:28,888 --> 00:11:30,720
Place is too new.

171
00:11:30,890 --> 00:11:33,450
He believes in a higher
power that can affect his life,

172
00:11:33,526 --> 00:11:34,824
like most people on the planet.

173
00:11:34,894 --> 00:11:37,955
True. On the other
hand, crucified himself.

174
00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:41,898
No canned tuna and I don't
think we have to worry about sushi.

175
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:45,961
No computer, no television,
no music. What does he do?

176
00:11:46,139 --> 00:11:49,473
He reads. Prayer has
been proven to aid recovery.

177
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,670
Only if the person knows
they're being prayed for.

178
00:11:52,645 --> 00:11:54,841
Means there's
no objective effect.

179
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:59,147
So faith comes from within.
Not exactly a newsflash.

180
00:12:08,027 --> 00:12:10,758
I guess worry is
good for the waistline.

181
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:19,705
It's not worry, it's starvation.

182
00:12:20,273 --> 00:12:22,418
His tooth didn't fall out because
of heavy metal poisoning,

183
00:12:22,442 --> 00:12:23,933
it fell out because
of malnutrition.

184
00:12:24,043 --> 00:12:25,534
He does have rhodococcus equi.

185
00:12:25,845 --> 00:12:27,404
Taub was right.

186
00:12:28,548 --> 00:12:30,949
He just didn't know why.

187
00:12:36,556 --> 00:12:38,548
It's locked! WILSON: I'm busy.

188
00:12:39,292 --> 00:12:40,726
I'll wait.

189
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:46,763
I really am busy.

190
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:48,892
Cuddy got me
the daughter's file.

191
00:12:49,035 --> 00:12:51,061
Well, not Cuddy,
exactly. Her signature.

192
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:54,468
Well, not exactly her signature.

193
00:12:56,542 --> 00:12:57,601
Another lie?

194
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:59,388
Thought you could
take a look at it for me.

195
00:12:59,412 --> 00:13:01,404
Maybe you hadn't
heard, I'm kind of busy.

196
00:13:01,481 --> 00:13:02,710
With what?

197
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:04,375
Sudoku. What do you think?

198
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:07,952
I'm the head of oncology
in a major hospital.

199
00:13:08,821 --> 00:13:12,258
And yet these files are
not from this hospital.

200
00:13:13,259 --> 00:13:16,752
These are from
Where-My-FiancÃ©e-Works Memorial.

201
00:13:16,829 --> 00:13:19,799
Sam's boss is doing a
clinical review of all of her files,

202
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:21,197
and she just wanted to make sure

203
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:23,221
everything's in order
before he starts on Monday.

204
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:26,031
Which explains why Sam
is too busy to look at my file.

205
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:29,439
If I don't help her, she can't
go to the wedding, and...

206
00:13:30,009 --> 00:13:31,569
We fell in love at
her cousin's wedding,

207
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,977
which is why I want to
propose to her at a wedding.

208
00:13:34,147 --> 00:13:36,309
And now, you have 60
seconds to berate me for that

209
00:13:36,382 --> 00:13:39,011
and for helping my
girlfriend with her homework.

210
00:13:39,118 --> 00:13:40,496
You don't want to
propose at a wedding.

211
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:42,955
Emotions running
high, people on edge.

212
00:13:43,022 --> 00:13:47,357
You want to try somewhere like
a Buddhist temple or an aquarium,

213
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,952
or a Buddhist aquarium.

214
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:52,431
That only took 10 seconds.

215
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,990
You can spend the rest
of the time on my file.

216
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,735
Rachel?

217
00:14:14,554 --> 00:14:17,149
Hey. How long
before you're home?

218
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:18,689
<i>Notlong.</i>

219
00:14:20,660 --> 00:14:22,891
Hey. Hey.

220
00:14:22,962 --> 00:14:23,962
Uh...

221
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:27,023
Yeah, you left your laptop on.

222
00:14:28,668 --> 00:14:32,002
I saw you today, at the hotel.

223
00:14:32,772 --> 00:14:34,468
Were you checking up on me?

224
00:14:35,441 --> 00:14:36,670
Yes.

225
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,105
Satisfied?

226
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:40,540
Yes.

227
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,241
Good.

228
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:45,742
That's it?

229
00:14:45,852 --> 00:14:47,787
You said you're
satisfied, that's enough.

230
00:14:48,955 --> 00:14:51,948
You're not wondering
why it started,

231
00:14:52,358 --> 00:14:54,403
that makes me think you
don't want to talk about this,

232
00:14:54,427 --> 00:14:55,725
which makes me think...

233
00:14:55,795 --> 00:14:57,263
You're being paranoid.

234
00:14:57,363 --> 00:14:59,525
You took your cell phone
with you into the bathroom

235
00:14:59,599 --> 00:15:00,999
when you took a
shower this morning.

236
00:15:03,469 --> 00:15:06,633
I made a new friend, online.

237
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,474
In a support group.

238
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:12,338
A guy?

239
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:13,436
Yes.

240
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,439
Support group for what?

241
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,779
For people with
unfaithful spouses.

242
00:15:25,191 --> 00:15:27,717
Why didn't you tell us
you were starving yourself?

243
00:15:27,794 --> 00:15:30,263
Well, I wasn't trying to.

244
00:15:30,329 --> 00:15:33,322
I'm on a tight budget and
it seemed like an okay diet.

245
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,560
You seem to be feeling better.

246
00:15:36,636 --> 00:15:39,299
Not really, my
