00:28:56,802 --> 00:28:58,464
This round's on the bro?

495
00:29:08,013 --> 00:29:09,013
Um...

496
00:29:10,549 --> 00:29:12,882
I'm sorry about your daughter.

497
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,178
I never meant to hurt her.

498
00:29:16,688 --> 00:29:18,384
You just thought
she'd change my mind.

499
00:29:20,926 --> 00:29:22,895
I was surprised she didn't.

500
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:26,523
So was I.

501
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:31,095
I didn't tell you the truth.

502
00:29:31,703 --> 00:29:34,002
When I said I'm
not afraid to die.

503
00:29:34,706 --> 00:29:37,369
But you're going
straight to heaven, so...

504
00:29:38,543 --> 00:29:41,240
That's what I believe.
But I'm human.

505
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:43,508
So you know you may be wrong.

506
00:29:45,083 --> 00:29:47,552
How could you do
what you just did?

507
00:29:50,355 --> 00:29:55,020
That's why we have beliefs, so
we can still see the right thing to do

508
00:29:55,093 --> 00:29:57,062
when we're blinded
with doubt and fear.

509
00:29:58,430 --> 00:30:03,130
Our beliefs define us. If
we lose them, who are we?

510
00:30:11,877 --> 00:30:15,541
Look, I'm sorry. I didn't
mean for it to go that way.

511
00:30:19,718 --> 00:30:23,655
You think I'm being
selfish but I'm not.

512
00:30:26,325 --> 00:30:30,160
He makes me feel better
about me and about us.

513
00:30:31,163 --> 00:30:33,598
Well, that is hard to believe

514
00:30:34,966 --> 00:30:38,403
because all I feel
right now is betrayed.

515
00:30:39,137 --> 00:30:40,264
I never wanted that.

516
00:30:40,339 --> 00:30:41,339
Good.

517
00:30:42,074 --> 00:30:45,841
Because just like you asked
me to stop my behavior,

518
00:30:45,977 --> 00:30:48,310
I'm asking you to stop this.

519
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:53,713
No?

520
00:30:53,785 --> 00:30:55,447
I'm not gonna lie to you.

521
00:30:55,587 --> 00:30:57,283
Is this revenge?

522
00:30:58,824 --> 00:31:00,224
I don't know.

523
00:31:00,292 --> 00:31:02,989
But I do know that it's
something I need right now.

524
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:15,971
What would you wear?

525
00:31:18,343 --> 00:31:20,039
I'm a sucker for the white gown.

526
00:31:22,647 --> 00:31:25,879
Traditionally for
young, first-time brides.

527
00:31:26,118 --> 00:31:29,646
Well, I may not be
young but I'd be first-time.

528
00:31:31,857 --> 00:31:34,292
That is a lie.

529
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:43,293
You were married before.
In 1987, for six days.

530
00:31:45,470 --> 00:31:47,837
Your knowledge of New Jersey
divorce law made me suspicious,

531
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:48,999
so I looked it up.

532
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:53,035
So this was all your trap?

533
00:31:53,678 --> 00:31:57,240
Trap's primitive, I
prefer inveiglement.

534
00:31:57,349 --> 00:32:01,844
Anyway, the point is, I lied to
you, you lied to me, I forgive you.

535
00:32:09,027 --> 00:32:10,393
Well played.

536
00:32:16,568 --> 00:32:18,696
You're tired, aren't
you? All those files.

537
00:32:19,371 --> 00:32:22,500
No, no, I was thinking...

538
00:32:24,676 --> 00:32:27,510
I mean, if those two even have
the slightest chance of making it,

539
00:32:27,579 --> 00:32:30,515
then we have to be a sure thing.

540
00:32:31,416 --> 00:32:33,681
And we've already
made all our mistakes.

541
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:35,519
And...

542
00:32:41,693 --> 00:32:45,289
I've come to realize
that I love you

543
00:32:45,363 --> 00:32:47,264
even more than I thought I did.

544
00:32:47,599 --> 00:32:50,728
Sam, will you marry me again?

545
00:32:55,941 --> 00:32:58,410
Wow. I don't even
know what to say.

546
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:00,143
I have a suggestion.

547
00:33:00,579 --> 00:33:03,242
Where did this even
come from? When did you...

548
00:33:05,917 --> 00:33:08,386
You just came to realize?

549
00:33:08,453 --> 00:33:11,651
What made you love me even more?

550
00:33:12,958 --> 00:33:19,455
Everything you've done, your
work, your sense of morality.

551
00:33:22,634 --> 00:33:24,102
The five cases.

552
00:33:24,903 --> 00:33:28,101
I not only agree with
what you did, I admire it.

553
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:30,072
I didn't do anything.
You already asked me

554
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:32,610
about the files and
I told you the truth.

555
00:33:32,677 --> 00:33:35,010
I know, and I get it.

556
00:33:36,314 --> 00:33:37,646
You don't believe me.

557
00:33:37,782 --> 00:33:42,015
I believe that you are
a wonderful person.

558
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,349
Who lies and cheats.

559
00:33:43,421 --> 00:33:44,445
No, Sam.

560
00:33:44,523 --> 00:33:47,152
Listen, I'm on your side.

561
00:33:48,293 --> 00:33:50,023
I can't believe this.

562
00:33:52,497 --> 00:33:55,160
What? Sam. Sam, don't do this.

563
00:34:21,026 --> 00:34:22,790
So how many do you think?

564
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:25,363
At least three.

565
00:34:26,231 --> 00:34:27,961
Hat-trick Chase.

566
00:34:29,167 --> 00:34:32,865
See? Life of the bachelor.
All of the sex, none of the guilt.

567
00:34:33,672 --> 00:34:37,336
It's not over, okay? I
just really miscalculated.

568
00:34:38,343 --> 00:34:40,403
I thought she'd forgiven
me for everything

569
00:34:40,512 --> 00:34:45,007
but all those hurt feelings,
they never really went away.

570
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:49,914
That makes a lot more sense.

571
00:34:51,056 --> 00:34:54,549
Ignore him, he just got an idea.

572
00:34:56,728 --> 00:34:58,492
I have one more test to run.

573
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:04,426
Uh, I hate weddings.

574
00:35:22,454 --> 00:35:23,547
Won't be long now.

575
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:29,060
You'll be staring down the
yawning void before you know it.

576
00:35:29,461 --> 00:35:31,589
You came from a
wedding to tell me that?

577
00:35:31,696 --> 00:35:36,691
No, I came from a
wedding to run a PET scan.

578
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:38,561
Thought you'd given up on me.

579
00:35:38,737 --> 00:35:41,901
I have. PET scan
was for your daughter.

580
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:44,298
I was wrong about her.

581
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,745
She did have glioblastoma.

582
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:53,443
And she still does.
Cancer never went away.

583
00:35:54,586 --> 00:35:57,988
Yes, it did. They
tested her every year.

584
00:35:58,223 --> 00:35:59,816
With a CT scan

585
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:04,323
which misses all the tiny little
tumors that a PET scan doesn't.

586
00:36:04,429 --> 00:36:08,423
You made a mistake. She
does not have cancer anymore.

587
00:36:08,733 --> 00:36:11,498
I ran it twice, no mistake.

588
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:17,106
Looks like God broke your deal.

589
00:36:20,779 --> 00:36:22,270
I'm sorry.

590
00:36:23,682 --> 00:36:25,514
But I'm also right.

591
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:31,512
You're a bastard.

592
00:36:37,862 --> 00:36:39,660
Do whatever you want to me.

593
00:36:41,466 --> 00:36:42,832
Good call.

594
00:36:49,808 --> 00:36:52,437
Surprised you've got enough
strength to come to work today.

595
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:55,309
Thirty-six hours is long
enough for me to recover.

596
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:58,016
And not nearly long enough
for this guy to be getting better.

597
00:36:58,116 --> 00:37:00,881
House wanted us checking
every 12 hours anyway.

598
00:37:01,820 --> 00:37:02,844
Sorry I took off on you.

599
00:37:03,555 --> 00:37:04,614
Twice.

600
00:37:05,156 --> 00:37:07,716
First one was my bad.
Second one I had no choice.

601
00:37:08,993 --> 00:37:10,222
It was a threesome.

602
00:37:11,629 --> 00:37:12,961
They're overrated.

603
00:37:14,132 --> 00:37:15,896
He's bluffing. He's bluffing.

604
00:37:17,736 --> 00:37:19,170
Get House.

605
00:37:20,572 --> 00:37:23,906
Got something to show you.
Your daughter's PET scan.

606
00:37:25,477 --> 00:37:26,740
It's clean.

607
00:37:27,812 --> 00:37:29,041
She's fine.

608
00:37:30,548 --> 00:37:31,846
My bad.

609
00:37:32,383 --> 00:37:34,545
Got her mixed up
with Marion Silver.

610
00:37:35,186 --> 00:37:38,748
Marisa Silva. That's
believable, right?

611
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:43,085
Anyhow, good news for
you, bad news for Mr. Silver.

612
00:37:43,194 --> 00:37:46,995
You tricked me. God
didn't break our deal, I did.

613
00:37:48,233 --> 00:37:51,226
You led me into
temptation and I followed.

614
00:37:51,336 --> 00:37:53,100
And God will
punish you for that.

615
00:37:53,204 --> 00:37:55,105
He has to. 'Cause if he didn't,

616
00:37:55,373 --> 00:37:56,932
it'd make you
wonder, wouldn't it?

617
00:37:57,041 --> 00:37:58,202
He will.

618
00:37:58,576 --> 00:38:01,774
Well, that's why I'm
so confused by this.

619
00:38:02,847 --> 00:38:06,443
This is your MRI. Shows
incremental improvement.

620
00:38:06,551 --> 00:38:07,678
You're getting better.

621
00:38:09,354 --> 00:38:10,834
I double-checked
the name on this one.

622
00:38:11,456 --> 00:38:16,360
But it's not all good news.
This patient is screwed.

623
00:38:16,795 --> 00:38:19,765
Technical term is
dead as a doornail.

624
00:38:20,231 --> 00:38:21,290
Who is that?

625
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:22,623
God.

626
00:38:23,434 --> 00:38:25,027
You broke your deal with him

627
00:38:25,103 --> 00:38:27,047
but your daughter's fine
and you're getting better.

628
00:38:27,071 --> 00:38:30,564
Nothing bad happened.
Which can only mean one thing,

629
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:31,974
there is no God.

630
00:38:33,278 --> 00:38:36,043
'Course, if your daughter
gets hit by a meteorite today,

631
00:38:36,114 --> 00:38:38,276
I would have some
serious egg on my face.

632
00:38:40,385 --> 00:38:43,913
You're smiling. I assume
that means you're miserable.

633
00:38:44,823 --> 00:38:46,485
It means I'm happy.

634
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,890
This doesn't mean
God doesn't exist,

635
00:38:50,962 --> 00:38:53,488
it just means
he's truly merciful.

636
00:38:55,233 --> 00:38:57,065
My beautiful Marisa was right,

637
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,300
God is all about love.

638
00:38:59,437 --> 00:39:03,101
Punishment is proof of God and
no punishment is proof of God.

639
00:39:04,075 --> 00:39:05,839
Ingenious argument.

640
00:39:07,745 --> 00:39:09,441
Faith isn't an argument.

641
00:39:12,750 --> 00:39:14,685
I'd like to see my daughter.

642
00:39:24,262 --> 00:39:26,026
Everyone else knew?

643
00:39:26,698 --> 00:39:29,668
Everyone I could trust. So, yes.

644
00:39:31,269 --> 00:39:33,966
If you had told me,
he'd be dead by now.

645
00:39:35,206 --> 00:39:37,198
So why do I still
want to tell the truth?

646
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:41,676
Either you're naÃ¯ve, or you have
scruples. I'm not sure which is worse.

647
00:39:42,447 --> 00:39:45,474
This is insane. We
can't work like this.

648
00:39:46,684 --> 00:39:47,879
I can.

649
00:39:54,125 --> 00:39:55,149
Sam?

650
00:39:56,294 --> 00:39:58,854
Sorry, I was hoping to be
done before you got home.

651
00:39:59,664 --> 00:40:01,792
We had a fight.
We had one fight.

652
00:40:02,667 --> 00:40:04,966
And I admitted I was wrong.

653
00:40:05,036 --> 00:40:06,636
We can talk about
it, we can get over it.

654
00:40:06,671 --> 00:40:07,695
This is about trust.

655
00:40:07,805 --> 00:40:10,138
I never lied to you
about anything.

656
00:40:10,208 --> 00:40:12,837
I know, and I
always trusted you.

657
00:40:15,346 --> 00:40:17,110
Maybe we could
talk to a counselor.

658
00:40:17,181 --> 00:40:18,877
You said that helped
after our divorce.

659
00:40:18,983 --> 00:40:21,680
It did, and I think
I changed a lot.

660
00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:25,156
And I haven't. This is my fault?

661
00:40:26,658 --> 00:40:28,923
I know where this is going.

662
00:40:28,993 --> 00:40:30,552
And I don't want
to go there again.

663
00:40:33,364 --> 00:40:37,597
You're quitting, Sam.
You're quitting again.

664
00:40:39,070 --> 00:40:40,834
So I guess you haven't
changed that much.

665
00:41:10,068 --> 00:41:11,195
Good work today.

666
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:14,135
Don't even think your
patient's gonna sue.

667
00:41:15,807 --> 00:41:17,435
Looks like everybody's happy.

668
00:41:22,113 --> 00:41:23,638
I've been an idiot.

669
00:41:25,984 --> 00:41:28,044
I got this argument
stuck in my head.

670
00:41:28,119 --> 00:41:32,420
If everybody lies, then trust is
not only unfounded and pointless,

671
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:34,425
it's fictional.

672
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:38,759
But trust is not an argument
that can be won or lost.

673
00:41:39,130 --> 00:41:44,330
Maybe I just have to suspend
my cynicism and believe.

674
00:41:46,437 --> 00:41:48,463
Maybe it's time I
took a leap of faith.

675
00:41:52,777 --> 00:41:54,143
I'm sorry.

676
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:57,110
I won't lie to you again.

677
00:41:59,617 --> 00:42:00,983
Thank you.

678
00:42:16,601 --> 00:42:18,126
Sam left me.

679
00:42:18,503 --> 00:42:20,131
What a moron.

680
00:42:22,006 --> 00:42:23,975
Too soon. I'm still
in love with her.

681
00:42:25,143 --> 00:42:26,441
I meant you.

682
00:42:27,845 --> 00:42:30,440
Do you have a drink? Or drinks?

683
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:32,347
Cuddy's coming over.

684
00:42:37,555 --> 00:42:39,217
Does she know you're here?

685
00:42:40,725 --> 00:42:42,557
I apologized to her.

686
00:42:48,032 --> 00:42:50,467
Good for you.

687
00:42:53,204 --> 00:42:56,368
Not really, I lied.

688
00:43:00,478 --> 00:43:03,971
I just took your advice.
Too bad you didn't.

689
00:43:07,652 --> 00:43:09,143
Good for you.
